<section id="gettingstarted_editors_object_class">
	<title>Object class editor</title>
	<para>
		The object class editor is the one-stop shop where you can
		define all aspects of your object class.
	</para>
	<para>
		<screenshot>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata scale="50"
						fileref="images/editors_object-class-editor-overview.png"
						format="PNG" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</screenshot>
	</para>
	<para>
		The
		<emphasis role="strong">Overview</emphasis>
		page is where the user can edit the properties of the object
		class.
	</para>
	<para>User can edit:</para>
	<para>
		<itemizedlist spacing="normal" mark="bullet">
			<listitem>the name</listitem>
			<listitem>the OID</listitem>
			<listitem>the description</listitem>
			<listitem>the superior class</listitem>
			<listitem>the class type</listitem>
			<listitem>if the object class is obsolete</listitem>
			<listitem>
				the mandatory attributes (add and remove)
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				the optional attributes (add and remove)
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	</para>
	<para>
		<screenshot>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata scale="50"
						fileref="images/editors_object-class-editor-source-code.png"
						format="PNG" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</screenshot>
	</para>
	<para>
		The
		<emphasis role="strong">Source code</emphasis>
		page is where the user can see the result of his actions in the
		Overview page and what source code will be generated in the
		schema file.
	</para>
</section>